[5] New Mexico
Date: 17 Feb 2016
Source: New Mexico Livestock Board [edited]
https://www.nmlbonline.com/index.php?id=15


Update on EHV-1 virus at Sunland Park Racetrack
---------
To simplify our reporting on the rapidly-changing EHV-1 virus outbreak at the Sunland Park Racetrack, we will update the list below regularly with the most current information. While the situation warrants, we will also e-mail blast this information as it is updated.

Number of horses diagnosed positive for the EHV-1 virus to-date: 72 in New Mexico and 2 in Texas
Number of horses released today from the isolation barn: 2
Number of exposed barns that have been returned to non-exposed status to-date: 17
List of facilities within the quarantine perimeter:
Sunland Park Racetrack and Frontera Training Center.

Biosecurity measures among horsemen and women are still necessary, such as taking temperatures twice a day, handwashing, washing/disinfecting anything a horse has touched or could touch, etc.

The article below is from the American Association of Equine Practioners in Q&A format providing lots of useful information regarding the EHV virus. We have also linked to the original press release and a 1 Feb 2016 overview, though the information above may be considered a later update..

Original NMLB press release 22 Jan 2016
American Association of Equine Practitioners FAQ for EHV

